# Phase 8 — widget.js (the UI hook)

## What's here

```
frontend/
  widget.js        -- the embeddable widget itself (vanilla JS, no build step)
  demo.html         -- standalone test page (homepage / collection / product modes)
  test_widget.js    -- jsdom smoke tests, run after every widget.js change
```

## How it works

One `<script>` tag, dropped in once on dotandkey.com:

```html
<script src="https://cdn.dotandkey.com/advisor/widget.js"
        data-api-base="https://advisor.dotandkey.com"></script>
```

- Renders inside a **Shadow DOM** — the host page's CSS can never leak in,
  and the widget's CSS can never leak out. No class-name collisions with
  Dot & Key's existing theme, ever.
- No build step. No webpack/vite/React needed to ship this — it's one
  plain JS file, which is also why `data-api-base` is read off the
  script tag itself rather than requiring a config file.
- Detects page context from `window.location.pathname`: `/products/*` →
  product mode, everything else → homepage/collection mode.
- Profile ID is a `crypto.randomUUID()` stored in `localStorage` —
  no cookies (Safari's ITP caps JS-set cookies at 7 days; localStorage
  has no such cap, which matters for the 60-day profile TTL).

## Local testing

**1. Fast smoke test (no browser needed)** — run after every change:

```fish
cd frontend
npm install jsdom --no-save   # one-time
node test_widget.js
```

This runs the actual widget code in a real DOM implementation (jsdom) and
checks: shadow DOM creation, bubble→panel expand/collapse, SSE token
streaming, chip rendering from the backend's structured `done` event data,
product-page detection, and top-pick-vs-remaining card styling. It mocks
`fetch` — no backend needs to be running for this.

**2. Real browser test** — do this before shipping any change, since
jsdom can't catch everything (mobile viewport quirks, Safari's localStorage
behavior in private mode, real animation rendering):

```fish
# from the project root, with the backend running (./scripts/start_dev.fish)
cd frontend
python3 -m http.server 5500
```

Open `http://localhost:5500/demo.html` — it has a mode switcher (top-left)
to preview homepage, sunscreen-collection, and product-page contexts. The
demo page stubs the Shopify `.json` endpoint so product mode works without
a real Shopify store behind it.

## Known v1 limitations (flagged, not blocking)

- **Add to cart is a stub.** Product SKUs in the graph (`DK_CCNS`) aren't
  mapped to real Shopify variant IDs yet — that mapping doesn't exist in
  our data (flagged earlier as a data gap). The button currently shows
  "Added ✓" and logs to console; wire up Shopify's Storefront API
  `cartLinesAdd` mutation once that mapping exists. Search `TODO(shopify)`
  in `widget.js`.
- **Returning-user "Things have changed" chip** sends a generic message
  rather than resetting the stored profile — there's no `/profile/reset`
  endpoint yet. Low priority since the 60-day TTL already handles staleness.
- **No retry on a dropped SSE connection.** If `/chat`'s stream cuts out
  mid-response (network blip), the widget shows a generic error and the
  user has to resend. Acceptable for v1; a reconnect-with-backoff would
  be the v2 improvement.

## What's NOT done yet (separate phases)

- Admin CRUD API (Phase 9) — dynamic product add/edit via the graph.
- Semantic response cache (Phase 6) — the ~65% latency win from
  caching repeated profile→recommendation queries.
- Real Shopify cart integration (see "Add to cart is a stub" above).